The Texas State Bobcats fell to the Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns 70-61 during the White Out game in Strahan Arena, dropping their record to 12-10. Kaden Gumbs led the Bobcats with 17 points, while Coleton Benson and Joshua O'Garro contributed 10 points each. Despite leading by 10 at one point, Texas State struggled offensively in the second half, allowing Louisiana to pull ahead.
- Kaden Gumbs scored 17 points and added six rebounds.
- Texas State led by 10 points twice in the first half but ended up trailing at halftime.
- Both teams have a record of 5-5 in Sun Belt Conference play.
- Texas State is set to face conference leader Arkansas State next.
The Bobcats will compete against top-ranked Arkansas State on Saturday, looking to improve their record and standings in the conference.
Bottom LineDespite a strong start, Texas State's inability to maintain momentum led to their defeat; they must regroup for their upcoming challenge against Arkansas State.
